.TH "snd_hda_codec_amp_init_stereo" 9 "snd_hda_codec_amp_init_stereo" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hda_codec_amp_init_stereo \- initialize the stereo AMP value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_hda_codec_amp_init_stereo
.BI "(struct hda_codec *codec "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t nid "  ","
.BI "int dir "  ","
.BI "int idx "  ","
.BI "int mask "  ","
.BI "int val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
the HDA codec
.IP "nid" 12
NID to read the AMP value
.IP "dir" 12
#HDA_INPUT or #HDA_OUTPUT
.IP "idx" 12
the index value (only for input direction)
.IP "mask" 12
bit mask to set
.IP "val" 12
the bits value to set
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Call \fBsnd_hda_codec_amp_init\fP for both stereo channels.
